race.comment: RECON (6) is coming off a narrow win at Mornington last time out, good when in the market behind a subsequent city winner fresh. He can improve again at start number six and prove hard to hold out late. HARALDUS (5) did enough first up at Pakenham when midfield. Getting to 1200m is much more suitable and his best form reads well. He boasts two wins second-up and he looks poised to strike. JACKS ON ICE (1) can mix his form but was good last time at Kyneton in a handy race. Can bounce off that effort as he reaches his peak and he can play a major role. MRS ARTIE (3) resumes with an imposing record over further, she'll be working home late.
